      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1139</offset>
        <text>The efficiency of fertilization, defined as the ratio of the carbon export to the amount of iron supplied, was at least ten times higher than previous estimates from short-term blooms induced by iron-addition experiments.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">9</infon>
        <offset>1361</offset>
        <text>This result sheds new light on the effect of long-term fertilization by iron and macronutrients on carbon sequestration, suggesting that changes in iron supply from below--as invoked in some palaeoclimatic and future climate change scenarios--may have a more significant effect on atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations than previously thought.
</text>
